"title": "2069: Jesus Christ, pre-eminence of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "2069: jesus christ, pre-eminence of",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Jesus Christ excels over all of creation and reigns supreme over everthing in the created order.</p>\n<h2>The scope of Jesus Christ's pre-eminence</h2>\n<h3>Over all people</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John17:2\">JHN 17:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:31-Matt25:32\">MAT 25:31–25:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom10:12\">ROM 10:12</a></p>\n<h3>Over his enemies</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:25-1Cor15:26\">1CO 15:25–15:26</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:32-Acts2:35\">ACT 2:32–2:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps110:1\">PSA 110:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:8\">EPH 4:8</a> <em>Paul probably interpreted “captives” to refer to the spiritual enemies of Christ defeated at the cross.</em></p>\n<h3>Over every power and authority</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col2:15\">COL 2:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:21\">EPH 1:21</a></p>\n<h3>Over all traditions and institutions</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:8\">MAT 12:8</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark2:28\">MRK 2:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke6:5\">LUK 6:5</a></p>\n<h3>Over all things</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:28\">1CO 15:28</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt11:27\">MAT 11:27</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke10:22\">LUK 10:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt28:18\">MAT 28:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:35\">JHN 3:35</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John13:3\">JHN 13:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John16:33\">JHN 16:33</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts10:36\">ACT 10:36</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil3:21\">PHP 3:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb2:8\">HEB 2:8</a></p>\n<h2>The pre-eminence of Jesus Christ in relation to others</h2>\n<h3>To other prophets</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt3:11\">MAT 3:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:41\">MAT 12:41</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:32\">LUK 11:32</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:26-John1:27\">JHN 1:26–1:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:30\">JHN 1:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:30\">JHN 3:30</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb1:1-Heb1:2\">HEB 1:1–1:2</a></p>\n<h3>To the patriarchs</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:17\">JHN 1:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:52-John8:58\">JHN 8:52–8:58</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb3:3-Heb3:6\">HEB 3:3–3:6</a></p>\n<h3>To Aaron and other high priests</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb8:1-Heb8:6\">HEB 8:1–8:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb4:14\">HEB 4:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb6:20\">HEB 6:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb7:23\">HEB 7:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb7:26-Heb7:28\">HEB 7:26–7:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:11-Heb9:14\">HEB 9:11–9:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:24-Heb9:26\">HEB 9:24–9:26</a></p>\n<h3>To angels</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet3:22\">1PE 3:22</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb1:4-Heb1:14\">HEB 1:4–1:14</a></p>\n<h3>To other lords and kings</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev17:14\">REV 17:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim6:15\">1TI 6:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev19:16\">REV 19:16</a></p>\n<h2>Descriptions of Jesus Christ's pre-eminence</h2>\n<h3>He is the head</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col2:10\">COL 2:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:9-Eph1:10\">EPH 1:9–1:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:22\">EPH 1:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:15\">EPH 4:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:23-Eph5:24\">EPH 5:23–5:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:18\">COL 1:18</a></p>\n<h3>He is the capstone</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt21:42\">MAT 21:42</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark12:10-Mark12:11\">MRK 12:10–12:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke20:17\">LUK 20:17</a> <em>By so saying Jesus Christ applied this verse to himself. The capstone/cornerstone was the most significant stone of a building's structure.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps118:22\">PSA 118:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:11\">ACT 4:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:20\">EPH 2:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:7\">1PE 2:7</a></p>\n<h3>He is the Chief Shepherd</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John10:11\">JHN 10:11</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb13:20\">HEB 13:20</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet5:4\">1PE 5:4</a></p>\n<h2>The reasons for Jesus Christ's pre-eminence</h2>\n<h3>His divine origin</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:31\">JHN 3:31</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:1-John1:2\">JHN 1:1–1:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John17:24\">JHN 17:24</a></p>\n<h3>His equality with the Father</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John10:30\">JHN 10:30</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:19\">COL 1:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col2:9\">COL 2:9</a></p>\n<h3>His authority derives from the Father</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John5:22-John5:27\">JHN 5:22–5:27</a></p>\n<h3>He possesses the rights of the firstborn</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:15-Col1:17\">COL 1:15–1:17</a></strong> <em>As the firstborn son has the rights and privileges of an heir, so Jesus Christ is heir of all things by virtue of his pre-existence and sonship.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:29\">ROM 8:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb1:6\">HEB 1:6</a></p>\n<h3>He has a superior name</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:9\">PHP 2:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:12\">ACT 4:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb1:4\">HEB 1:4</a></p>\n<h3>He is the First and the Last</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev1:17\">REV 1:17</a></strong> <em>This title implies that all things are summed up in Christ and find their purpose in him.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev2:8\">REV 2:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev22:13\">REV 22:13</a></p>\n<h2>Examples of events whereby Jesus Christ's pre-eminence is recognised</h2>\n<h3>His entry into Jerusalem</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt21:4-Matt21:9\">MAT 21:4–21:9</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark11:7-Mark11:10\">MRK 11:7–11:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke19:35-Luke19:38\">LUK 19:35–19:38</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:12-John12:15\">JHN 12:12–12:15</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech9:9\">ZEC 9:9</a></p>\n<h3>His resurrection</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:4\">ROM 1:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:21-1Cor15:23\">1CO 15:21–15:23</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev1:5\">REV 1:5</a></p>\n<h3>His exaltation to the Father's right hand</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:31\">ACT 5:31</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:33\">ACT 2:33</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:55\">ACT 7:55</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:20-Eph1:21\">EPH 1:20–1:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:8-Eph4:10\">EPH 4:8–4:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:9-Phil2:11\">PHP 2:9–2:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:1\">COL 3:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb8:1\">HEB 8:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:12\">HEB 10:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet3:22\">1PE 3:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev3:21\">REV 3:21</a></p>",
